|ShortSummary = Ben, the new shop manager, finds himself in a tight spot after a shop accident breaks the most valuable part of the 1964 Plymouth Barracuda restoration, then the crew lets off some steam in the first ever shop vs. yard demolition derby.
|LineColor = 7b0c0c
}}
|Aux4 =
|ShortSummary = What Jason McClure thought was a simple 1955 Ford F-100 restoration turns into anything but as a new shop manager and engine problems make the going tough for the Desert Valley Auto Parts crew.
|LineColor = 7b0c0c
}}
|Aux4 =
|ShortSummary = Jason strikes gold when he discovers that a 1966 Chevrolet Chevelle he bought is actually a rare SS model. But can the crew find a high roller willing to buy the restored car at their auction?
|LineColor = 7b0c0c
}}
|Aux4 =
|ShortSummary = The crew at Desert Valley face one of their greatest challenges in the shape of a 1950 Studebaker Champion, when rare parts and urban legends about the car's hidden features send the crew scrambling.
|LineColor = 7b0c0c
}}
|Aux4 =
|ShortSummary = A 1950 Cadillac is slow to get moving, and a Route 66 renovation gives Ron a change of heart that surprises everyone.
|LineColor = 7b0c0c
}}
